TASK LIST: Convert project to full-stack with MongoDB backend

1) Backend - Core
- Create Express server that connects to MongoDB (Mongoose)
- Add environment config (.env) with MONGODB_URI, DB_NAME, JWT_SECRET, PORT
- Implement authentication routes: /api/auth/signup, /api/auth/login
- Issue JWT tokens on signup/login (stateless auth)
- Implement links CRUD routes: /api/links (GET public/sample, GET user, POST create, DELETE)
- Protect routes with middleware that validates JWT

2) Backend - Models
- User schema: name, email (unique), passwordHash, avatar, theme, createdAt
- Link schema: userId (ref User), title, url, order, visible, createdAt

3) Frontend - Routing & Pages
- Add React Router to the front-end
- Create pages: Landing (public sample profile), Login, Signup, Dashboard (user links), Profile (user settings, theme), Link editor
- Update `index.html` and `src/main.jsx` to use BrowserRouter
- Update `src/App.jsx` to include Routes and navigate without full reload

4) Frontend - Auth & API
- Add `src/api/client.js` to centralize API base URL and auth header handling
- Implement login/signup forms that call `/api/auth` endpoints and store JWT in localStorage
- Add logout functionality that clears auth and redirects to landing
- Protect dashboard/profile routes: if no token, redirect to login

5) Frontend - Links
- Create UI to list, add, delete user's links calling `/api/links` endpoints
- On landing (public access), show sample profile/links when no user is specified

6) Theme (Light/Dark)
- Add theme toggle button in `Header` (navbar)
- Store selected theme in user profile (persist to backend) and in localStorage for unauthenticated users
- Apply theme classes to `document.documentElement` or root container

7) UX Flow
- Landing shows sample profile + Get Started CTA
- Get Started navigates to Login/Signup
- After login/signup, navigate to Dashboard and load user links
- Provide logout button in navbar

8) Security & Flexibility
- Use password hashing (bcrypt)
- Use JWT with configurable secret and expiry
- Design APIs to return minimal user info (id, name, email, theme)
- Keep code modular: separate `server/routes`, `server/models`, `src/pages`, `src/api`

9) Dev & Scripts
- Add server start scripts in root `package.json`: `start:server`, `dev:server`
- Provide `.env.example` and instructions to run both frontend and backend locally

10) Future Enhancements (suggested)
- Add refresh tokens or cookie-based auth for improved security
- Add file uploads for avatars (e.g., S3) and image handling
- Add pagination/sorting for links and analytics endpoints
- Add role-based access (admin)

Instructions for agent completing tasks
- Follow this list in order. Implement backend endpoints first and test with Postman.
- Add frontend pages with stub UI that calls backend; once endpoints work, improve UI/UX.
- Keep changes minimal and modular; add unit tests for backend if possible.
